(34,	1,	'2026-03-09 08:06:07',	'2026-03-09 08:06:07',	'<p>Nuts are among the most nutrient-dense foods available, packing protein, healthy fats, fibre and a wide range of vitamins and minerals into a small, portable package.</p>\n\n<p>Almonds are the go-to for sustained energy. Rich in vitamin E, magnesium and slow-releasing carbohydrates, a small handful before a workout or a long meeting can keep you focused and fuelled for hours.</p>\n\n<p>Walnuts stand out for their omega-3 content — unusually high for a plant food. These essential fats support brain health and reduce inflammation, making walnuts a smart daily habit.</p>\n\n<p>Cashews are lower in fat than most nuts and rich in iron and zinc, making them particularly valuable for people following a plant-based diet. Their creamy texture also makes them a versatile ingredient in cooking.</p>\n\n<p>Buying organic matters more with nuts than many people realise. Conventional nuts are often heavily treated with fungicides during storage. Organic certification ensures a cleaner product from farm to bag.</p>',	'Best Organic Nuts for Energy',	'Almonds, walnuts, cashews — we break down which nuts give you the best nutritional bang for your buck.',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'28-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2026-03-09 08:06:07',	'2026-03-09 08:06:07',	'',	28,	'http://server-coomendem.local/?p=34',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(35,	1,	'2026-03-09 08:06:26',	'2026-03-09 08:06:26',	'<p>Cold-pressed juice has become a premium product in health food stores, but the price difference compared to standard pasteurized juice raises a fair question: is it actually better for you?</p>\n\n<p>The case for cold-pressing is rooted in the production process. Traditional juicers generate heat through friction, which can degrade heat-sensitive vitamins and enzymes. Cold-press machines use hydraulic pressure to extract juice slowly, preserving more nutrients in the final product.</p>\n\n<p>Pasteurization — heating juice to kill bacteria — extends shelf life significantly but does reduce certain vitamins, particularly vitamin C and some B vitamins. The extent depends on temperature and duration.</p>\n\n<p>In terms of taste, cold-pressed juices tend to have a fresher, more vibrant flavour. The difference is most noticeable with green juices and delicate fruit blends.</p>\n\n<p>The trade-off is shelf life and cost. Cold-pressed juices typically last three to five days refrigerated and cost significantly more to produce. For everyday drinking, a good quality pasteurized organic juice is still a healthy choice. Cold-pressed is worth the premium when you want maximum nutrition in a specific blend.</p>',	'Cold-Pressed vs Pasteurized Juice',	'Is cold-pressed really worth the premium? We compare nutrition, taste and shelf life side by side.',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'29-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2026-03-09 08:06:26',	'2026-03-09 08:06:26',	'',	29,	'http://server-coomendem.local/?p=35',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(36,	1,	'2026-03-09 08:06:32',	'2026-03-09 08:06:32',	'<p>Seasonal eating means choosing foods that are naturally ready to harvest at the time you\'re buying them. It sounds simple — and it is — but the benefits ripple out in ways that might surprise you.</p>\n\n<p>Produce picked in season and sold locally travels far shorter distances, which means it reaches you fresher and with more of its nutrients intact. Out-of-season produce is often picked early and ripened artificially in transit, which affects both flavour and nutritional value.</p>\n\n<p>Seasonally grown food is also less resource-intensive. Growing strawberries in a heated greenhouse in January requires enormous amounts of energy. The same strawberries grown outdoors in June are far more environmentally efficient.</p>\n\n<p>Getting started is straightforward. Visit a local farmers\' market and buy what\'s available — that\'s your seasonal guide right there. Alternatively, look up a seasonal food calendar for your region and use it when planning your weekly meals.</p>\n\n<p>Seasonal eating also naturally connects you to variety. When you commit to eating what\'s available now, you find yourself cooking with ingredients you might otherwise overlook — and that\'s where some of the best discoveries happen.</p>',	'Seasonal Eating: A Beginner\'s Guide',	'Eating with the seasons is better for your body and the planet. Here\'s how to get started simply.',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'30-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2026-03-09 08:06:32',	'2026-03-09 08:06:32',	'',	30,	'http://server-coomendem.local/?p=36',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(37,	1,	'2025-03-04 19:00:00',	'2025-03-04 19:00:00',	'<p>Going organic is one of the best decisions you can make for your health and the planet. Organic farming avoids synthetic pesticides and fertilizers, relying instead on natural processes to grow food that is cleaner, more nutritious and kinder to the environment.</p>\n\n<p>Studies consistently show that organic produce contains higher levels of antioxidants and essential nutrients compared to conventionally grown alternatives. By choosing organic, you\'re reducing your exposure to harmful chemicals and supporting farming practices that protect soil health and biodiversity.</p>\n\n<p>Beyond personal health, the environmental benefits are profound. Organic farms support richer ecosystems, reduce water pollution and contribute to lower carbon emissions. When you buy organic, you\'re voting with your wallet for a food system that works with nature rather than against it.</p>\n\n<p>Getting started doesn\'t have to be expensive. Focus on the \"Dirty Dozen\" — the twelve fruits and vegetables with the highest pesticide residues — and prioritise buying those organic. Then gradually expand your choices as your budget allows.</p>\n\n<p>The journey to organic living is a gradual one. Small, consistent choices add up over time, both for your wellbeing and for the health of the world around you.</p>',	'Reasons to Go Organic',	'Discover how organic products can improve your health and support the environment around you.',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'reasons-to-go-organic',	'',	'',	'2026-03-09 08:18:14',	'2026-03-09 08:18:14',	'',	0,	'http://server-coomendem.local/reasons-to-go-organic/',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
